data.title: Canada Gazette
data.meta_description: The Canada Gazette is the official newspaper of the Government of Canada. You can learn about new statutes, new and proposed regulations, administrative board decisions and public notices. Find out how government departments, businesses and other Canadian organizations can publish their public notices
data.text:
Find an edition

Search by keyword to find Canada Gazette publications since 1998. For publications between 1841 and 1997, visit Library and Archives Canada collection: The Canada Gazette (1841 to 1997).
